      "Physical access control mechanisms: Proximity/RFID cards (HID/iClass) = passive cards read at ≤10 cm; Active RFID = powered, longer range; Smart cards (CAC, PIV) = processor + memory with cryptographic capability; Mantraps/access control vestibules = two interlocked doors preventing tailgating; badge cloning = copying RFID RF signal (mitigated by Faraday pouches and shielded wallets); NFC smartphone credentials increasingly replacing physical badges in enterprise environments",
      "OIDC vs SAML vs OAuth 2.0: OAuth 2.0 = delegation/authorisation protocol (issues scoped access tokens, not authentication); OIDC (OpenID Connect) = authentication layer on top of OAuth 2.0 — issues ID token (JWT) proving user identity; SAML = XML-based federated authentication — dominant for enterprise SSO between IdP and SP; OIDC preferred for modern web/mobile apps; SAML preferred for enterprise and legacy; JWT = header.payload.signature (base64url encoded — payload is NOT encrypted by default)",
